You know that “omg so cute” moment when you spot a piece of jewellery? Totally get it — but before you hit *buy*, here’s what to check.

Design matters, of course — but so does what it’s made of. Always read the material description, especially if you’re wearing it daily.

If it says “alloy,” pause. That could mean anything from nickel (hello, skin irritation) to lead — and no one wants that surprise.

And if it’s super cheap? There’s probably a catch. Low prices often mean quick tarnish, green fingers, or something even worse.
